-- Italian Stocks: Buzzi, Cementir, Mediobanca, Monte dei Paschi, UBI Move
-- Francesca Cinelli
-- 2010-07-07T14:00:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-07/fastweb-fiat-shares-may-move-in-milan-today-italian-stock-market-preview.html

          
          
             Italy’s benchmark  FTSE MIB Index  rose
245.66, or 1.3 percent, to 19,602.32 as of 3:28 p.m. in Milan.  
 The following stocks are among the most active in the
Italian market today.  
 Banca Monte dei Paschi di Siena SpA  (BMPS IM) rose 1.8
percent to 93.65 cents, as a measure for European banking stocks
reversed losses earlier today.  Intesa Sanpaolo SpA  (ISP IM)
gained 1.5 percent to 2.21 euros.  Unione di Banche Italiane ScpA 
(UBI IM) rose 2.2 percent to 7.55 euros.  
 Buzzi Unicem SpA  (BZU IM), Italy’s second-biggest cement
maker, sank 20 cents, or 2.4 percent, to 8 euros. CRH Plc, the
world’s second-largest maker and distributor of building
materials, said a sales decline may be “somewhat greater” than
previously forecast.  Cementir Holding SpA  (CEM IM), the cement
maker owned by Italy’s Caltagirone family, dropped 4.75 cents,
or 2.1 percent, to 2.23 euros.  
 Italcementi SpA  (IT IM), Italy’s biggest cement maker, lost
4 cents, or 0.7 percent, to 6.09 euros.  
 Mediobanca SpA  (MB IM) rose for a second day, gaining 16.5
cents, or 2.6 percent, to 6.41 euros. Evolution Securities
initiated coverage of the country’s biggest publicly traded
investment bank with a “buy” recommendation.  
 Yoox SpA  (YOOX IM) gained 13 cents, or 2.2 percent, to 6.08
euros, a fourth straight increase. Berenberg Bank initiated
coverage of the Internet fashion retailer with a “buy”
recommendation and a price estimate of 7.5 euros.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
